I for one think we should all seek a little dignity in our life.  We call each other a lot of things like kids do when they run out of vocabulary.<br><br>
Let's get a bit more positive.  I am sure after 25 years of professional effort there are many positives in your life along with some of the negatives.  The positives and the negatives is why we are all here.<br><br>
We are on the left and right of the situation and the ground we seek is somewhere in the middle.  All is not lost yet.  This site has proven that fact.<br><br>
I suggest we regroup and take a fresh look at where we are going.  No one will prevent you from coming along.<br><br>
We are all guilty of typing before we think.  Brain in gear first.  The Asian method of spending more time thinking than commenting would serve us all.<br><br>
It has been a learning experience with you on board.  It is up to me to shift through what I want to keep.<br><br>
There is only one section of your dialogue that I struggle with.  The one wishing the enemy to have brought about our demise.  I should assume that was used to bring about the anger you were looking for.<br><br>
If we would stop trying to hurt then we could grow.<br><br>
My real info for you Doc.  The others have it.  Check me out.  I am more real than you think.<br>

